    <div class="hero-bg"></div>
    <div class="container hero-content">
      <div class="state-badge">
        <span class="state-flag">&#127466;&#127465;</span>
        <span>Idaho-Based Agency</span>
      </div>

      <h1>Idaho Trucking Insurance</h1>
      <p class="hero-tagline">Local Experts Who Know Idaho Law</p>
      <p class="hero-sub">RMS Truck Insurance is based right here in Idaho. We're not a national call center with an Idaho phone number. We're your neighbors who know Idaho Code, Idaho roads, and Idaho trucking operations.</p>

      <div class="trust-badges">
        <div class="badge"><span class="badge-icon">&#10003;</span> Based in Idaho</div>
        <div class="badge"><span class="badge-icon">&#10003;</span> 1,000+ Truckers Helped</div>
        <div class="badge"><span class="badge-icon">&#10003;</span> 5-Minute COIs</div>
        <div class="badge"><span class="badge-icon">&#10003;</span> Idaho Code Experts</div>
      </div>

      <a href="tel:208-800-0640" class="hero-cta">
        <span class="cta-label">Get Your Idaho Quote</span>
        <span class="cta-number">208-800-0640</span>
      </a>

      <p class="hero-note">When you call, you get someone in your time zone who understands what it means to run Lookout Pass in January.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- IDAHO REGULATIONS -->
  <section class="regulations">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-tag">What National Agents Miss</span>
        <h2>Idaho's Unique Trucking Regulations</h2>
        <p class="section-intro">Idaho has trucking regulations that differ significantly from federal standards. Most insurance agents quote you a policy and move on. We make sure you understand the rules that affect your operation.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="reg-grid">
        <div class="reg-card highlight">
          <h3>105,500-Pound State Weight Limit</h3>
          <p class="reg-cite">Idaho Code 49-1001</p>
          <p>Idaho allows a <strong>maximum gross vehicle weight of 105,500 lbs</strong> on state highways - well above the federal 80,000 lb limit.</p>
          <table class="reg-table">
            <tr><td>Idaho state highways</td><td><strong>105,500 lbs</strong></td></tr>
            <tr><td>Interstate (I-84, I-90, I-15, I-86)</td><td>80,000 lbs</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Single axle</td><td>20,000 lbs</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Single wheel</td><td>10,000 lbs</td></tr>
          </table>
          <a href="/idaho-weight-limits-permits/" class="reg-link">Full weight limits guide &rarr;</a>
        </div>

        <div class="reg-card chain-widget-container">
          <ChainLawWidget />
        </div>

        <div class="reg-card alert">
          <h3>Medical Certificate Enforcement</h3>
          <p class="reg-cite">Effective April 1, 2025</p>
