        <div class="corridor-card">
          <span class="corridor-name">I-84</span>
          <span class="corridor-route">The Main Artery</span>
          <p>Interstate 84 runs the width of Southern Idaho - from Oregon through Boise, Twin Falls, and on to Utah. Pacific Northwest produce heading east, Port of Portland freight moving inland, cross-country runs connecting I-80 and I-90.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="corridor-card">
          <span class="corridor-name">I-90</span>
          <span class="corridor-route">The Northern Crossings</span>
          <p>Includes Lookout Pass and Fourth of July Pass - two locations where Idaho's chain law applies. Seattle/Spokane freight heading east, Coeur d'Alene operations, Montana connections.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="corridor-card">
          <span class="corridor-name">US-95</span>
          <span class="corridor-route">North-South Spine</span>
          <p>Connects Lewiston through Boise to Nevada - key for Northern Idaho timber and agricultural freight.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="cities-section">
        <h3>The Population Centers</h3>
        <div class="cities-grid">
          <div class="city"><strong>Boise</strong> - Metro construction, distribution hub, HP/Micron supply chain</div>
          <div class="city"><strong>Twin Falls</strong> - Food processing (Chobani, Glanbia), dairy transport</div>
          <div class="city"><strong>Pocatello</strong> - Rail intermodal, phosphate mining</div>
          <div class="city"><strong>Idaho Falls</strong> - INL contractors, agriculture, eastern corridor hub</div>
          <div class="city"><strong>Nampa/Caldwell</strong> - Treasure Valley logistics, agricultural processing</div>
          <div class="city"><strong>Lewiston</strong> - Timber, Port of Lewiston barge freight</div>
          <div class="city"><strong>Coeur d'Alene</strong> - Northern Idaho hub, I-90 corridor operations</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- REQUIREMENTS -->
  <section class="requirements">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-tag">What You Need</span>
        <h2>Idaho Trucking Insurance Requirements</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="table-wrap">
        <table class="req-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Requirement</th>
              <th>Details</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>USDOT Number</td><td>Required for all commercial vehicles</td></tr>
            <tr><td>MC Number</td><td>Required for for-hire interstate carriers</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Minimum Liability</td><td><strong>$750,000</strong> for general freight</td></tr>
            <tr><td>BMC-91 Filing</td><td>Proof of insurance filed with FMCSA</td></tr>
            <tr><td>BOC-3 Filing</td><td>Process agent designation (required)</td></tr>
            <tr><td>UCR Registration</td><td>Annual unified carrier registration</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="idaho-specific">
        <h3>Idaho-Specific Requirements</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>IFTA Registration</strong> - International Fuel Tax Agreement for Idaho and other states</li>
          <li><strong>IRP Registration</strong> - International Registration Plan for apportioned plates</li>
          <li><strong>HVUT (Form 2290)</strong> - Required for vehicles 55,000+ lbs gross weight. File with IRS.</li>
          <li><strong>Motor Carrier Services:</strong> 208-334-8611 for IRP/IFTA questions</li>
        </ul>
        <a href="/idaho-commercial-registration/" class="reg-link">Complete registration guide &rarr;</a>
      </div>

      <div class="section-cta">
        <p><strong>RMS handles the federal filings.</strong> When we bind your policy, your BMC-91 files within 10 minutes. Your BOC-3 files the same day. You don't chase paperwork - we do.</p>
        <a href="tel:208-800-0640" class="btn">Call 208-800-0640</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- NEW AUTHORITY -->
  <section class="new-authority">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header centered">
        <span class="section-tag">New Authorities</span>
        <h2>Starting a Trucking Company in Idaho?</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="timeline">
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <span class="day">Day 1</span>
          <p>Apply for USDOT and MC numbers ($300 FMCSA fee)</p>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-connector"></div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <span class="day">Days 1-17</span>
          <p>20-21 day waiting period begins</p>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-connector"></div>
        <div class="timeline-item highlight">
          <span class="day">Day 18-19</span>
          <p>RMS binds your insurance and files your BMC-91</p>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-connector"></div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <span class="day">Day 21</span>
          <p>Authority goes active. You're legal to haul.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="rms-difference">
        <h3>The Idaho Advantage</h3>
        <p>As an Idaho-based company, we can meet you in person if needed. Complex situation? Questions about your authority? We're local. That matters when you're trying to get your business off the ground.</p>
        <p><strong>What you'll need for a quote:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Driver information (CDL, MVR, experience)</li>
          <li>Equipment details (year, make, model, VIN)</li>
          <li>Operation type (what you'll haul, where you'll run)</li>
          <li>USDOT number (or we can help you apply)</li>
          <li>Valid medical certificate (remember: April 2025 OOS enforcement)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- COVERAGE -->
  <section class="coverage">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-tag">Coverage</span>
        <h2>Coverage Options for Idaho Truckers</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="coverage-grid">
        <div class="coverage-card required">
          <span class="coverage-badge">Required</span>
          <h3>Auto Liability</h3>
          <p>Damage/injury you cause to others. $750K minimum for interstate.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="coverage-card">
          <span class="coverage-badge">If Financed</span>
          <h3>Physical Damage</h3>
          <p>Your truck - collision, theft, fire, vandalism.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="coverage-card">
          <span class="coverage-badge">Usually</span>
          <h3>Cargo Insurance</h3>
          <p>The freight you're hauling. Required by most brokers.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="coverage-card">
          <span class="coverage-badge">Optional</span>
          <h3>Bobtail / NTL</h3>
          <p>Driving without a trailer, personal use.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="coverage-card">
          <span class="coverage-badge">Sometimes</span>
          <h3>General Liability</h3>
          <p>Non-trucking business incidents.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="idaho-coverage">
        <h3>Idaho-Specific Coverage Considerations</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Winter coverage:</strong> Physical damage matters when Lookout Pass gets icy - chain law exemption doesn't mean weather exemption</li>
          <li><strong>Heavy haul:</strong> 105,500 lb loads on state highways need proper cargo coverage</li>
          <li><strong>Agricultural endorsements:</strong> Livestock haulers may need specific cargo coverage for animals</li>
          <li><strong>Logging operations:</strong> Specialized equipment coverage for timber hauling</li>
          <li><strong>Permit load coverage:</strong> Oversize/overweight operations under Idaho Code 49-1004</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PRICING -->
  <section class="pricing">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header centered">
        <span class="section-tag">Pricing</span>
        <h2>How Much Does Idaho Trucking Insurance Cost?</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="price-box">
        <p class="price-range">For new authorities with a single truck, expect <strong>$12,000-$18,000 per year</strong> for a standard package with $750K liability.</p>
        <p>That includes: Auto liability ($750,000), Cargo insurance ($100,000), Physical damage (depends on truck value)</p>
      </div>

      <div class="factors-grid">
        <div class="factor">
          <h4>Driving Experience</h4>
          <p>2+ years CDL experience = better rates</p>
        </div>
        <div class="factor">
          <h4>MVR (Driving Record)</h4>
          <p>Clean record vs. violations matters significantly</p>
        </div>
        <div class="factor">
          <h4>Equipment Age</h4>
          <p>Newer trucks = higher physical damage, but better liability rates</p>
        </div>
        <div class="factor">
          <h4>Cargo Type</h4>
          <p>General freight vs. hazmat vs. specialized</p>
        </div>
        <div class="factor">
          <h4>Operating Radius</h4>
          <p>Local Idaho vs. nationwide</p>
        </div>
        <div class="factor">
          <h4>Weight</h4>
          <p>105,500 lb operations vs. standard 80K</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="section-cta centered">
        <p>Same carriers, better service. 5-minute COIs. 10-minute filings. Someone who knows Idaho Code 49-948 when you ask about chains.</p>
        <a href="tel:208-800-0640" class="btn">Get Your Idaho Quote</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <FAQSection faqs={faqs} title="Idaho Trucking Insurance Questions" />

  <!-- RESOURCES -->
  <section class="resources">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header centered">
        <span class="section-tag">Resources</span>
        <h2>Idaho Trucking Resources</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="resource-grid">
        <a href="/idaho-chain-laws/" class="resource-card">
          <h3>Idaho Chain Laws Guide</h3>
          <p>Complete breakdown of Idaho Code 49-948 - the three passes, requirements, and all exemptions.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/idaho-weight-limits-permits/" class="resource-card">
          <h3>Idaho Weight Limits & Permits</h3>
          <p>105,500 lb state limit, commodity exemptions, permit types, and damage liability.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/idaho-commercial-registration/" class="resource-card">
          <h3>Idaho Commercial Registration</h3>
          <p>IRP, IFTA, UCR, and HVUT - everything you need to stay compliant.</p>
        </a>
      </div>

      <div class="external-resources">
        <h3>Official Idaho Resources</h3>
        <table class="resource-table">
          <tr>
            <td>Idaho Motor Carrier Services (IRP/IFTA)</td>
            <td><strong>208-334-8611</strong></td>
          </tr>
